      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZOE ELLA (2) is racing well with four top-five finishes in succession, the latest effort a second at this track over 2090m. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Meets some better types this time but a win is not out of the question. SOHO TIGER LILY (1) has been most impressive of late and she made it two in a row when successful at her latest appearance over 1680m at Launceston, getting home by 3.5 metres. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. OH NO NEVER AGAIN (9) finished fifth two runs ago then suffered interference and broke when a distant 11th over 1609m at this track at the latest appearance. It doesn't get any easier but he is talented enough to be competitive. KNOCK OUT NZ (8) is in the mix at his first run since finishing fourth over 2200m at Launceston nine weeks ago.",
